The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Duda of Poland and President Biden of the United States during a visit to the Presidential Palace in Warsaw, Poland. President Duda thanked President Biden for his recent visit to Kyiv, Ukraine, which boosted the morale of the defenders of Ukraine and sent a signal to those who violate international rules. He expressed gratitude for the United States' commitment to global security and its role in restoring freedom and democracy in Poland and Europe. President Duda also highlighted Poland's efforts to provide security to its allies and its support for Ukraine. President Biden emphasized the importance of the NATO alliance and the United States' commitment to Ukraine. He praised Poland for its support of Ukraine and announced plans to build nuclear power plants in Poland to bolster its energy security. President Biden also acknowledged the strong connection between Polish and American people and expressed confidence in further developing the partnership between the two countries.